               <head>Zad al-musafirin</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Zād al-musāfirīn by Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083116 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15661-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656480.0x000001 viaf_220924367">Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="viaf_220924367" type="supplied">محمد مهدی بن علی نقی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20103">Zād al-musāfirīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20103">زاد المسافرين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A guide to preservation of health and self-treatment for travellers, by Muḥammad Mahdī ibn ‘Alī Naqī. The work was completed at Isfahan in 1141/1728, during the Afghan invasion,
                for 
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7707" role="pat">Mīrzā Muḥammad Ismā‘īl</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>It comprises two parts (maṭlab): on preventive health and hygiene, and on the treatment of certain ailments treatable without the aid of a physician.</p>
                        <p>The present manuscript is slightly incomplete at the end.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
